  "prompt": "Who whave my number on watsapp?",
  "response": "On WhatsApp, the people who have your phone number and have saved it in their contacts will be able to see your profile information (such as your profile picture and status) if your privacy settings allow it. Additionally, anyone who has your phone number can message you on WhatsApp, provided you haven't blocked them.\n\nTo manage who can see your information on WhatsApp:\n\n1. Open WhatsApp and go to **Settings** (on iOS, it\u2019s in the bottom-right corner; on Android, it\u2019s in the top-right menu).\n2. Tap **Account**, then **Privacy**.\n3. Here, you can control who can see your **Last Seen**, **Profile Photo**, **About**, and **Status**:\n   - **Everyone**: Anyone with your number can see it.\n   - **My Contacts**: Only people in your contact list can see it.\n   - **Nobody**: No one can see it (except for your Last Seen, which would still be visible to people you\u2019ve messaged recently).\n\nIf you\u2019re concerned about privacy, it\u2019s a good idea to review these settings and adjust them to your comfort level. Remember, if someone has your phone number and you haven\u2019t blocked them, they can still message you on WhatsApp.",
